text: This pattern is more common to the entities which fall into the UNI category. Therefore, that might make the exact extraction of UNI and FUND entities more confusing. Moreover, many Indian Universities contain the name of individuals, e.g., Rajiv Gandhi University, which can cause confusion of the UNI category with the IND category. Generally, no improvement in increasing the size of the corpus for the FUND category can be explained by the ambiguous nature of the entities which fall into the FUND category and their semantical proximity with other types of entities. Analysis of the extracted entities showed that many entities were extracted correctly, but were assigned to the wrong category [CITATION_1].
